I"P<p>Tianqi Li (pronunciation: [tɪ-entʃi: ‘li:]) is a second-year Ph.D. student in <a href="https://econ.unc.edu/">Department of Economics</a> in <a href="https://www.unc.edu/">University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill</a> in the United States. His current research interests include Microeconometrics Theory and Application, Urban Economics, Nonparametric Estimation, Machine Learning.</p>

<p>In 2019, He achieved his bachelor’s degree in Mathematical Economics (Double major in Economics and Mathematics) in <a href="http://ems.whu.edu.cn/">School of Economics and Management</a> in <a href="https://en.whu.edu.cn/index.htm">Wuhan University</a> in China. His advisor for undergraduate dissertation (High-speed railway for Econ and LSTM network for Math) was Professor <a href="https://sites.google.com/site/jbcui2013">Jingbo Cui</a>.</p>
